post_text:
WESTWOOD JUBILATION 2020

Through much discussion during the past 72 hours, it has been decided that we must cancel Westwood’s Jubilation Show Choir Invitational on Saturday, March 14th, 2020.

Less than 48 hours ago we were optimistic that we could move forward, but with the current events surrounding COVID-19 we must err on the side of caution.

It is a tough decision because everyone deserves their opportunity to shine at our great event. We are grateful for not only all of the participating schools and judges, but all of the volunteers that make Jubilation a success each year. With that, we want everyone to be healthy. May Jubilation 2021 be the best yet!
text:
WESTWOOD JUBILATION 2020

Through much discussion during the past 72 hours, it has been decided that we must cancel Westwood’s Jubilation Show Choir Invitational on Saturday, March 14th, 2020.

Less than 48 hours ago we were optimistic that we could move forward, but with the current events surrounding COVID-19 we must err on the side of caution.

It is a tough decision because everyone deserves their opportunity to shine at our great event. We are grateful for not only all of the participating schools and judges, but all of the volunteers that make Jubilation a success each year. With that, we want everyone to be healthy. May Jubilation 2021 be the best yet!

post_text: All salt deliveries are being done on September 28th and 29th. Attached the map for deliveries. There will be 3 delivery times, Saturday 9am to 1pm which will be the River area and the town of Sloan, 1pm to 4pm which is north of town and the town of Salix and Browns Lake, and then Sunday from 1pm-5pm for everything East of town. This year there will not be calls ahead of time to let you know when we are coming. We will be in the area during those times. If you are not home, the salt will be left on the step or driveway. Please contact your salesperson to have it put where they want. If they are there or have left instructions we will accommodate that as needed.
